  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan Technical Assistance Program</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Programme d&apos;assistance technique pour l&apos;Afghanistan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Ce programme permet au Canada de r&#xE9;pondre rapidement et efficacement aux demandes du gouvernement de l&apos;Afghanistan pour le soutien technique et des conseils. Il vise &#xE0; renforcer les capacit&#xE9;s du gouvernement afghan &#xE0; g&#xE9;rer des institutions gouvernementales et &#xE0; offrir des services aux citoyens. Le programme comprend l&apos;&#xE9;tablissement du Bureau canadien d&#x2019;appui gouvernance (BCAG) &#xE0; Kaboul. Le BCAG recrute et d&#xE9;ploie des d&apos;experts techniques canadiens et internationaux pour aider les minist&#xE8;res afghans &#xE0; acqu&#xE9;rir les comp&#xE9;tences et l&apos;exp&#xE9;rience n&#xE9;cessaires afin de planifier, de mettre en &#x153;uvre et d&#x2019;&#xE9;valuer leurs activit&#xE9;s de mani&#xE8;re efficace.</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This program makes it possible for Canada to respond promptly and effectively to requests from the Government of Afghanistan for technical support and advice. The goal of the program is to strengthen the Government of Afghanistan&#x2019;s ability to manage government institutions and deliver services to citizens. The program includes establishing the Canadian Governance Support Office (CGSO) in Kabul. The CGSO recruits and deploys Canadian and international technical experts to help Afghan ministries build the skills and experience they need to effectively plan, implement, and evaluate their activities.</narrative>
  </description>
